"n.作伪证，发假誓 【英】 n. 伪证，假誓(false swearing) 【考】 calumny : assertion / false swearing : oath / perjury : deposition (testimony)(诽谤是假断言/伪誓 是假誓言/伪证是假证 词)反义词：truthful deposition(真实的作 证) 【例】 Committing perjury in court can result in a prison sentence. n. 伪证; 假誓 【参】jury(n 陪审团) 【类】calumny: assertion[representation] = false swearing: oath = perjury: deposition[testimony]诽谤是假断言 = 伪誓是假誓言 = 伪证是假证词 【反】truthful deposition(真实的作证) 【记】per 音:破 + jury 陪审团,把陪审团搞破搞乱通过做伪证,假誓 perjury (n.)  late 14c., ""act of swearing to a statement known to be false,"" via Anglo-French perjurie (late 13c.) and Old French parjurée ""perjury, false witness,"" both from Latin periurium ""a false oath,"" from periurare ""swear falsely,"" from per- ""away, entirely"" (see per) + iurare ""to swear"" (see jury (n.)). Related: Perjurious."
